title: Google\Cloud\Iot\V1\DeviceConfig
name: DeviceConfig
description:
The device configuration. Eventually delivered to devices.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.iot.v1.DeviceConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.version
params.description: [Output only] The version of this update. The version number is assigned by the server, and is always greater than 0 after device creation. The version must be 0 on the CreateDevice request if a config is specified; the response of CreateDevice will always have a value of 1.

params.name: data.cloud_update_time
params.description: [Output only] The time at which this configuration version was updated in Cloud IoT Core. This timestamp is set by the server.

params.name: data.device_ack_time
params.description: [Output only] The time at which Cloud IoT Core received the acknowledgment from the device, indicating that the device has received this configuration version. If this field is not present, the device has not yet acknowledged that it received this version. Note that when the config was sent to the device, many config versions may have been available in Cloud IoT Core while the device was disconnected, and on connection, only the latest version is sent to the device. Some versions may never be sent to the device, and therefore are never acknowledged. This timestamp is set by Cloud IoT Core.
